==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: naturalist
<hw>nat"u*ral*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>naturaliste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One versed in natural
science; a student of natural history, esp. of the natural history of
plants or animals; a botanist or zoologist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds or maintains the doctrine of
naturalism in religion.</def> <rj><au>H. Bushnell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naturalistic</ent>⟦br⟧
